==Overview== The Nagatsuka Kofun is a {{nihongo|''zenpō-kōen-fun''|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|2=ja|3=前方後円墳|4=ko|5=전방후원분|6=zh|7=前方後圓墳|lt=Zenpokoenfun|comement=second one attempting to fix this error|lt=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|comment=doing this because I need to differentiate it in piped links too with my new interwiki tool as not the ambiguous phrase keyhole shaped kofun|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun}}, which is shaped like a keyhole, having one square end and one circular end, when viewed from above. The tumulus is constructed in two-tiers and is located at an elevation of 10 meters on a [[:en:Fluvial terrace|river terrace]] between the [[Kiso River]] and its tributary, the Kanogawa River. It is the largest of the Maenami cluster of 15 tumuli in the same area. It was [[archaeological excavation|excavated]] by the Kani City Department of Education in 1982, 1986 and from 1995 to 1997. The tumulus was found to be 81 meters long, with a posterior circular portion 46 meters in diameter, 8.3 meters high, and a 25 meter wide by 5.9 meter high anterior rectangular portion. Neither ''[[fukiishi]]'' or ''[[:en:Haniwa|Haniwa]]'' were discovered, but the tumulus had traces of a five-meter wide moat on its south and east sides.
